In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Capacity is the Capacity in liters of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Tank.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.IsLevelLow is the Indicates if the Diesel Exhaust Fluid level is low. True if level is low. Definition of low is vehicle dependent.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Level is the Level of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid tank as percent of capacity. 0 = empty. 100 = full.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Range is the Remaining range in meters of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid present in the vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.DeltaPressure is the Delta Pressure of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.InletTemperature is the Inlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.OutletTemperature is the Outlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeCurrent is the Current charging current.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeLimit is the Target charge limit (state of charge) for battery.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePlugType is the Type of charge plug (charging inlet) available on the vehicle. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePortFlap is the Status of the charge port cover, can potentially be controlled manually.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeRate is the Current charging rate, as in kilometers of range added per hour.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeVoltage is the Current charging voltage, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsCharging is the True if charging is ongoing. Charging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from charger to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableConnected is the Indicates if a charging cable is physically connected to the vehicle or not.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableLocked is the Is charging cable locked to prevent removal.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsDischarging is the True if discharging (vehicle to grid) is ongoing. Discharging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from vehicle to charger/grid.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.MaximumChargingCurrent is the Maximum charging current that can be accepted by the system, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Mode is the Control of the charge process. MANUAL means manually initiated (plug-in event, companion app, etc). TIMER means timer-based. GRID means grid-controlled (eg ISO 15118). PROFILE means controlled by profile download to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the AC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.StartStopCharging is the Start or stop the charging process.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Temperature is the Current temperature of AC/DC converter converting grid voltage to battery voltage.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.TimeToComplete is the The time needed for the current charging process to reach Charging.ChargeLimit. 0 if charging is complete or no charging process is active or planned.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer is the Properties related to timing of battery charging sessions.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside DC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.Temperature is the Current temperature of DC/DC converter converting battery high voltage to vehicle low voltage (typically 12 Volts).
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Current is the Physical state of charge of the high voltage battery, relative to net capacity. This is not necessarily the state of charge being displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Displayed is the State of charge displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Average is the Current average temperature of the battery cells.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Max is the Current maximum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the hottest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Min is the Current minimum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the coldest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.LowerBound is the Lower bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 5% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.MostProbable is the Most probable road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. Exact meaning of most probable is implementation specific. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.UpperBound is the Upper bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 95% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.IsHeatingOn is the Mirror Heater on or off. True = Heater On. False = Heater Off.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.Pan is the Mirror pan as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Left Position. -100 = Fully Right Position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.Tilt is the Mirror tilt as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Upward Position. -100 = Fully Downward Position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Right.IsHeatingOn is the Mirror Heater on or off. True = Heater On. False = Heater Off.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Right.Pan is the Mirror pan as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Left Position. -100 = Fully Right Position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Right.Tilt is the Mirror tilt as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Upward Position. -100 = Fully Downward Position.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Trunk.Rear.IsLocked is the Is trunk locked or unlocked. True = Locked. False = Unlocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Trunk.Rear.IsOpen is the Trunk open or closed. True = Open. False = Closed.

In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeLimit is the Target charge limit (state of charge) for battery.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePlugType is the Type of charge plug (charging inlet) available on the vehicle. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePortFlap is the Status of the charge port cover, can potentially be controlled manually.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeRate is the Current charging rate, as in kilometers of range added per hour.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeVoltage is the Current charging voltage, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsCharging is the True if charging is ongoing. Charging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from charger to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableConnected is the Indicates if a charging cable is physically connected to the vehicle or not.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableLocked is the Is charging cable locked to prevent removal.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsDischarging is the True if discharging (vehicle to grid) is ongoing. Discharging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from vehicle to charger/grid.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.MaximumChargingCurrent is the Maximum charging current that can be accepted by the system, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Mode is the Control of the charge process. MANUAL means manually initiated (plug-in event, companion app, etc). TIMER means timer-based. GRID means grid-controlled (eg ISO 15118). PROFILE means controlled by profile download to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the AC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.StartStopCharging is the Start or stop the charging process.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Temperature is the Current temperature of AC/DC converter converting grid voltage to battery voltage.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.TimeToComplete is the The time needed for the current charging process to reach Charging.ChargeLimit. 0 if charging is complete or no charging process is active or planned.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer is the Properties related to timing of battery charging sessions.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside DC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.Temperature is the Current temperature of DC/DC converter converting battery high voltage to vehicle low voltage (typically 12 Volts).
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Current is the Physical state of charge of the high voltage battery, relative to net capacity. This is not necessarily the state of charge being displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Displayed is the State of charge displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Average is the Current average temperature of the battery cells.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Max is the Current maximum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the hottest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Min is the Current minimum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the coldest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.LowerBound is the Lower bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 5% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.MostProbable is the Most probable road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. Exact meaning of most probable is implementation specific. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.UpperBound is the Upper bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 95% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.IsHeatingOn is the Mirror Heater on or off. True = Heater On. False = Heater Off.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.Pan is the Mirror pan as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Left Position. -100 = Fully Right Position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.Tilt is the Mirror tilt as a percent. 0 = Center Position. 100 = Fully Upward Position. -100 = Fully Downward Position.

In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.TireAspectRatio is the Aspect ratio between tire section height and tire section width, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.TireDiameter is the Outer diameter of tires, in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.

In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelCount is the Number of wheels on the axle
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelDiameter is the Diameter of wheels (rims without tires), in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelWidth is the Width of wheels (rims without tires), in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.

In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.X is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver antenna relative to vehicle coordinate system. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = forward of rear axle. Negative values = backward of rear axle.
In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.Y is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver antenna relative to vehicle coordinate system. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = left of origin. Negative values = right of origin. Left/Right is as seen from driver perspective, i.e. by a person looking forward.
In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.Z is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver on Z-axis. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = above center of rear axle. Negative values = below center of rear axle.

In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.TireAspectRatio is the Aspect ratio between tire section height and tire section width, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.TireDiameter is the Outer diameter of tires, in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.TireWidth is the Nominal section width of tires, in mm, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.Wheel is the Wheel signals for axle
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelCount is the Number of wheels on the axle
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelDiameter is the Diameter of wheels (rims without tires), in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.
In VSS Vehicle.Chassis.Axle.Row1.WheelWidth is the Width of wheels (rims without tires), in inches, as per ETRTO / TRA standard.

In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.X is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver antenna relative to vehicle coordinate system. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = forward of rear axle. Negative values = backward of rear axle.
In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.Y is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver antenna relative to vehicle coordinate system. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = left of origin. Negative values = right of origin. Left/Right is as seen from driver perspective, i.e. by a person looking forward.
In VSS Vehicle.CurrentLocation.GNSSReceiver.MountingPosition.Z is the Mounting position of GNSS receiver on Z-axis. Axis definitions according to ISO 8855. Origin at center of (first) rear axle. Positive values = above center of rear axle. Negative values = below center of rear axle.

In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Capacity is the Capacity in liters of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid Tank.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.IsLevelLow is the Indicates if the Diesel Exhaust Fluid level is low. True if level is low. Definition of low is vehicle dependent.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Level is the Level of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid tank as percent of capacity. 0 = empty. 100 = full.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Range is the Remaining range in meters of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid present in the vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.DeltaPressure is the Delta Pressure of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.InletTemperature is the Inlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.OutletTemperature is the Outlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeCurrent is the Current charging current.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeLimit is the Target charge limit (state of charge) for battery.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePlugType is the Type of charge plug (charging inlet) available on the vehicle. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePortFlap is the Status of the charge port cover, can potentially be controlled manually.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeRate is the Current charging rate, as in kilometers of range added per hour.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeVoltage is the Current charging voltage, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsCharging is the True if charging is ongoing. Charging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from charger to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableConnected is the Indicates if a charging cable is physically connected to the vehicle or not.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableLocked is the Is charging cable locked to prevent removal.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsDischarging is the True if discharging (vehicle to grid) is ongoing. Discharging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from vehicle to charger/grid.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.MaximumChargingCurrent is the Maximum charging current that can be accepted by the system, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Mode is the Control of the charge process. MANUAL means manually initiated (plug-in event, companion app, etc). TIMER means timer-based. GRID means grid-controlled (eg ISO 15118). PROFILE means controlled by profile download to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the AC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.StartStopCharging is the Start or stop the charging process.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Temperature is the Current temperature of AC/DC converter converting grid voltage to battery voltage.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.TimeToComplete is the The time needed for the current charging process to reach Charging.ChargeLimit. 0 if charging is complete or no charging process is active or planned.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer is the Properties related to timing of battery charging sessions.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside DC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.Temperature is the Current temperature of DC/DC converter converting battery high voltage to vehicle low voltage (typically 12 Volts).
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Current is the Physical state of charge of the high voltage battery, relative to net capacity. This is not necessarily the state of charge being displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Displayed is the State of charge displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Average is the Current average temperature of the battery cells.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Max is the Current maximum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the hottest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Min is the Current minimum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the coldest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.LowerBound is the Lower bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 5% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.MostProbable is the Most probable road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. Exact meaning of most probable is implementation specific. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.ADAS.ESC.RoadFriction.UpperBound is the Upper bound road friction, as calculated by the ESC system. 95% possibility that road friction is below this value. 0 = no friction, 100 = maximum friction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Mirrors.Left.IsHeatingOn is the Mirror Heater on or off. True = Heater On. False = Heater Off.

In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.IsLevelLow is the Indicates if the Diesel Exhaust Fluid level is low. True if level is low. Definition of low is vehicle dependent.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Level is the Level of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid tank as percent of capacity. 0 = empty. 100 = full.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselExhaustFluid.Range is the Remaining range in meters of the Diesel Exhaust Fluid present in the vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.DeltaPressure is the Delta Pressure of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.InletTemperature is the Inlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.CombustionEngine.DieselParticulateFilter.OutletTemperature is the Outlet temperature of Diesel Particulate Filter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeCurrent is the Current charging current.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeLimit is the Target charge limit (state of charge) for battery.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePlugType is the Type of charge plug (charging inlet) available on the vehicle. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargePortFlap is the Status of the charge port cover, can potentially be controlled manually.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeRate is the Current charging rate, as in kilometers of range added per hour.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.ChargeVoltage is the Current charging voltage, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsCharging is the True if charging is ongoing. Charging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from charger to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableConnected is the Indicates if a charging cable is physically connected to the vehicle or not.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsChargingCableLocked is the Is charging cable locked to prevent removal.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.IsDischarging is the True if discharging (vehicle to grid) is ongoing. Discharging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from vehicle to charger/grid.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.MaximumChargingCurrent is the Maximum charging current that can be accepted by the system, as measured at the charging inlet.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Mode is the Control of the charge process. MANUAL means manually initiated (plug-in event, companion app, etc). TIMER means timer-based. GRID means grid-controlled (eg ISO 15118). PROFILE means controlled by profile download to vehicle.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the AC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.StartStopCharging is the Start or stop the charging process.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Temperature is the Current temperature of AC/DC converter converting grid voltage to battery voltage.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.TimeToComplete is the The time needed for the current charging process to reach Charging.ChargeLimit. 0 if charging is complete or no charging process is active or planned.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer is the Properties related to timing of battery charging sessions.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.PowerLoss is the Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside DC/DC converter.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.DCDC.Temperature is the Current temperature of DC/DC converter converting battery high voltage to vehicle low voltage (typically 12 Volts).
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Current is the Physical state of charge of the high voltage battery, relative to net capacity. This is not necessarily the state of charge being displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.StateOfCharge.Displayed is the State of charge displayed to the customer.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Average is the Current average temperature of the battery cells.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Max is the Current maximum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the hottest cell.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Temperature.Min is the Current minimum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the coldest cell.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos3.Tilt is the Tilting of seat relative to vehicle z-axis. 0 = seating is flat, seat and vehicle z-axis are parallel. Positive degrees = seat tilted backwards, seat z-axis is tilted backward.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
