In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.

In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.

In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
