In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos2.Tilt is the Tilting of seat relative to vehicle z-axis. 0 = seating is flat, seat and vehicle z-axis are parallel. Positive degrees = seat tilted backwards, seat z-axis is tilted backward.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.IsLevelLow is the Low level indication for washer fluid. True = Level Low. False = Level OK.
In VSS Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.WasherFluid.Level is the Washer fluid level as a percent. 0 = Empty. 100 = Full.
In VSS Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Intensity is the Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.
In VSS IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.IsWipersWorn is the Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.
In VSS Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.Mode is the Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.
In VSS System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.WiperWear is the Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.MaximumChargingCurrent.Phase3 is the Maximum AC charging current (rms) at inlet for Phase 3 that can be accepted by the system.
In VSS Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Mode is the Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.
In VSS Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS Vehicle.Powertrain.TractionBattery.Charging.Timer.Time is the Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Airbag.IsDeployed is the Airbag signals.
In VSS Lumbar is the Adjustable lumbar support mechanisms in seats allow the user to change the seat back shape.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Backrest.Lumbar is the Describes signals related to the backrest of the seat.
In VSS Recline is the Backrest recline compared to seat z-axis (seat vertical axis). 0 degrees = Upright/Vertical backrest. Negative degrees for forward recline. Positive degrees for backward recline.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Backrest.Recline is the Describes signals related to the backrest of the seat.
In VSS SideBolster is the Backrest side bolster (lumbar side support) settings.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Backrest.SideBolster is the Describes signals related to the backrest of the seat.
In VSS Angle is the Headrest angle, relative to backrest, 0 degrees if parallel to backrest, Positive degrees = tilted forward.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Headrest.Angle is the Headrest settings.
In VSS Height is the Position of headrest relative to movable range of the head rest. 0 = Bottommost position supported.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Headrest.Height is the Headrest settings.
In VSS Identifier is the Identifier attributes based on OAuth 2.0.
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos1.Occupant.Identifier is the Occupant data.
In VSS Length is the Length adjustment of seating. 0 = Adjustable part of seating in rearmost position (Shortest length of seating).

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS Length is the Length adjustment of seating. 0 = Adjustable part of seating in rearmost position (Shortest length of seating).
In VSS Vehicle.Cabin.Seat.Row1.Pos3.Seating.Length is the Describes signals related to the seating/base of the seat.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.

In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS DriveCurrent is the Actual current used by wiper drive.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.DriveCurrent is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Frequency is the Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Frequency is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsBlocked is the Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsBlocked is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsEndingWipeCycle is the Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsEndingWipeCycle is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsOverheated is the Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsOverheated is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsPositionReached is the Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsPositionReached is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiperError is the Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiperError is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS IsWiping is the Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.IsWiping is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS Mode is the Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.Mode is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS TargetPosition is the Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Front.Wiping.System.TargetPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
In VSS ActualPosition is the Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.
In VSS Vehicle.Body.Windshield.Rear.Wiping.System.ActualPosition is the Signals to control behavior of wipers in detail. By default VSS expects only one instance.
